OpenVPN

Support AES-GCM, AES-CTR and AES-XTS cipher modes.
For Debian/Ubuntu packages.

Reference:
  https://community.openvpn.net/openvpn/attachment/ticket/301
  [0001-Add-AEAD-cipher-modes.patch]

How to make the package:

*Debian 7.5 (wheezy) # add backports apt-line
  (in some directory)
  apt-get -d source openvpn
  tar xzf openvpn_2.3.2.orig.tar.gz
  cd openvpn-2.3.2
  tar xzf ../openvpn_2.3.2-7~bpo70+1.debian.tar.gz
  cp -a (this repository)/wheezy-backports/debian/* debian/
  debuild -uc -us

*Ubuntu 14.04 LTS (Trusty Tahr)
  (in some directory)
  apt-get -d source openvpn
  tar xzf openvpn_2.3.2.orig.tar.gz
  cd openvpn-2.3.2
  tar xzf ../openvpn_2.3.2-7ubuntu3.debian.tar.gz
  cp -a (this repository)/trusty/debian/* debian/
  debuild -uc -us

Example options:
  openvpn --cipher id-aes128-GCM --auth none ...

